<subSubSection id="DCD995E2ECB313B4346E6C3C40C25E22" pageId="18" pageNumber="135" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="E6B3F8ACBB1791550CB25A43EAB016A3" pageId="18" pageNumber="135" type="mainText">
Janzen (1974) observed that at two sites (below the dam at Temascal, 
<normalizedToken id="161C1324234BC9DE51FC7D79DCAA1DFB" originalValue="Río" pageId="18" pageNumber="135">Rio</normalizedToken>
<misspelling id="633B2661276CFB7DABCE063DD5F51CB7" corrections="[Ljava.lang.String;@433d19e0" pageId="18" pageNumber="135" type="misspelled">Chichicazapa</misspelling>
, and at Arroyo 
<misspelling id="7AA9510E8D29631F71D384CDEDDD0050" corrections="[Ljava.lang.String;@606de39c" pageId="18" pageNumber="135" type="misspelled">Enmedio</misspelling>
, between Temascal, Oaxaca and La 
<misspelling id="2B346EE26D5154739BF41D2340201326" corrections="[Ljava.lang.String;@4e7a4839" pageId="18" pageNumber="135" type="misspelled">Granja</misspelling>
, Veracruz, Mexico) 
<taxonomicName id="17851214F06297211CBD9F3AD4F74C2E" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Acacia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="18" pageNumber="135" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chiapensis">Acacia chiapensis</taxonomicName>
may hybridize with non-ant-acacias such as 
<taxonomicName id="4887FBC1A53FBE33E31988D1D1AB2B5B" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Acacia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="18" pageNumber="135" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macracantha">A. macracantha</taxonomicName>
. At this site, numerous plants occurred that were 
<misspelling id="7DB5B8431EEE6EB30062359E3EC1B7B1" corrections="[Ljava.lang.String;@3e1bbe6f" pageId="18" pageNumber="135" type="misspelled">mtermediate</misspelling>
in spine, leaf, and branching morphology between these two species. During the present study no hybrids involving 
<taxonomicName id="582B4481C670CA80AFC1C2F4F0BA7415" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Acacia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="18" pageNumber="135" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chiapensis">A. chiapensis</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="BD98E12F0DA774513BE56BE060675FCB" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Acacia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="18" pageNumber="135" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macracantha">A. macracantha</taxonomicName>
were found; however, on a recent trip to Temascal (
<date id="0FFD7902705AE1F1001062B87FD257AC" pageId="18" pageNumber="135" value="1991-05">May 1991</date>
) the authors collected hybrid specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="006915329E2E633CF0E8D6B16EED2097" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Acacia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="18" pageNumber="135" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chiapensis × pennatula">A. chiapensis x A. pennatula</taxonomicName>
. Both parents were common in the pasture where the hybrid was collected and, except for 
<taxonomicName id="DFCC2DA5DA39BA3B0CF714C7B657E57C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Acacia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="18" pageNumber="135" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cornigera">A. cornigera</taxonomicName>
, were the only acacias in the area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
